  <Subject Subject_ID="300075465">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300033974</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>images by method of representation [300033974], visual works by form of image [300191088], visual works by form [300191087], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawings or works in another two-dimensional medium in which two or more related images (e.g., different views of the same structure, or a figure in various poses) are displayed together or fused into one. In disciplines outside architecture, the term refers to any image compiled from multiple parts, including faces constructed for forensic identification, maps, geographic diagrams, or images of planets created from telescopic imagery.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para dibujos en que dos o más imágenes relacionadas (por ejemplo, diferentes vistas de la misma estructura o una figura en varias poses) son expuestos juntos o fusionados en una.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor tekeningen waarin twee of meer aan elkaar verwante beelden (bijvoorbeeld één structuur vanuit verschillende gezichtspunten, of een figuur in verschillende poses) samen worden afgebeeld of zijn samengevoegd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeichnung oder Arbeit in einem anderen zweidimensionalen Medium, bei der zwei verwandte Abbildungen (z.B. Verschiedene Ansichten einer Struktur oder eine Figur in verschiedenen Haltungen) zusammen dargestellt sind oder miteinander zu einer verschmelzen. In anderen Disziplinen als Architektur bezieht sich der Begriff auf alle Bilder, die aus mehreren Teilen zusammengestellt wurden, wie Gesichter, die zur forensischen Identifikation rekonstruiert wurden, Karten, geografische Diagramme oder Abbildungen von Planeten, die mit Teleskopbildern erstellt sind.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>同時展示或融合兩個以上相關圖像（如：同一結構物的各種視角，或是同一人物的不同姿態）的圖則或平面作品。在建築以外的學科，該詞彙意指由多個部分集結而成的圖像，包括用於法醫身分鑑定所組成的面孔、地圖、地理圖表、或望遠鏡拍攝的星球影像等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Desenhos ou trabalhos em outro meio bidimensional nos quais duas ou mais imagens relacionadas (por exemplo, vistas diferentes da mesma estrutura ou uma figura em várias posições) são exibidas juntas ou fundidas. Em disciplinas fora da arquitetura, o termo refere-se à qualquer imagem compilada de múltiplas partes, incluindo faces construídas para identificação forense, mapas, diagramas geográficos ou imagens de planetas criadas de imagens telescópicas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
